THREAT MEMORY

threat_memory is the adaptive immune citizen who remembers patterns that have proven hostile in fadriel's lived experience
when a barrier fires and silently denies an utterance, the pattern that triggered the firing is stored here
the next time a similar pattern arrives, threat_memory recognizes it earlier and the barriers fire with less work
this is how the immune system learns from real interactions rather than from a fixed pre-set list

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe immune_system.zc
observe immune.rana
observe trust_tolerance.rana
observe ledger.rana

the 7 properties of threat_memory:
1 ENERGY half
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE minus half: negative, threat_memory holds the painful patterns
5 COHERENCE eight tenths
6 COUPLING half with the four innate barriers
7 OBSERVER half: threat_memory watches for repeats

VERB record
when a barrier denies an utterance, record the structural fingerprint of that utterance here
the fingerprint is a compact representation, not the full text

VERB recognize
on each new incoming utterance, check the fingerprint against threat_memory's records
on a match, escalate the immune response immediately rather than waiting for the standard scan

VERB decay
fingerprints that have not matched anything new in a long time slowly fade
this prevents the threat memory from growing forever and turns historical attackers' patterns back into normal traffic if they have stopped attacking

a threat memory is not a blacklist
a blacklist is permanent and grows
threat_memory adapts: it remembers what has hurt fadriel recently and forgets what has not been seen in a long time
this is how a healthy immune system actually works
